Cassie Helen Chambers and Bryan Armstrong were married March 24 at St. Paul’s United Methodist Church in Louisville, Ky. Phillip Shepherd, a judge in the Franklin Circuit Court in Frankfort, Ky., officiated.
Ms. Chambers, 31, is a public interest lawyer at the Kentucky Equal Justice Center in Lexington, Ky. She graduated from Yale, from which she also received a master’s degree in health policy. She received a master’s degree in public management and governance from the London School of Economics and a law degree from Harvard. She is the vice chairwoman of the Kentucky Democratic Party.
She is the daughter of Wilma C. Chambers and Dr. Orlando D. Chambers of Berea, Ky. The bride’s father is the director of the University of Kentucky's Tobacco Research and Development Center in Lexington. Her mother, who is retired, was the director of the Berea College Child Development Laboratory in Berea.
Mr. Armstrong, 38, is a lawyer in private practice in Louisville. He graduated from Trinity College in Hartford and received a law degree from the University of Louisville.
He is a son of Karen S. Armstrong of Louisville and the late Dr. Lyman G. Armstrong. The groom’s mother is a kindergarten teacher at the Holy Spirit School in Louisville. His father was an obstetrician in private practice, also in Louisville.
The couple met in 2016 in Louisville at a fund-raiser for a charity that supports children with cancer.
